article.headline: CCSU 77, UMBC 69
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- Kyle Vinales, Ken Horton and Robby Ptacek combined for 71 points in Central Connecticut State's 77-69 win over Maryland-Baltimore County on Tuesday night. UMBC (0-5) took a three point lead, 53-50, in the second half behind a Chandler Thomas layup with 11:02 left to play. But CCSU rallied, going on a 17-5 run, to take a 67-58 lead with 4:02 remaining in the second half. The Retrievers closed the gap to four, 67-63, but Vinales and Ptacek each hit four free throws to help seal the victory. Vinales led all scorers with 29 points while Ptacek and Horton each added 21. UMBC outshot CCSU (2-2) from the field, 45 percent (29 for 64) to 43 percent (24 for 56), and outrebounded the Blue Devils 41-33. But UMBC sent CCSU to the free throw line 30 times compared to just 10 attempts for the Retrievers.
